  <h1>🦷 Invisalign at Potomac Crown Dentistry – Confident Smiles Start Here</h1>

  <p>Are you ready to straighten your teeth discreetly and comfortably? At <strong>Potomac Crown Dentistry</strong>, we offer <strong>Invisalign</strong>—the clear aligner solution that fits seamlessly into your lifestyle. Whether you’re a teen, a working professional, or simply looking to improve your smile, Invisalign gives you the flexibility to align your teeth <em>without wires or brackets</em>.</p>

  <h2>Why Choose Invisalign?</h2>
  <p>Unlike traditional braces, Invisalign uses a series of custom-made, clear aligners that gradually shift your teeth into place. They're removable, easy to clean, and virtually invisible—so you can continue your day-to-day activities with confidence.</p>

  <h3>Benefits of Invisalign:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Clear, discreet aligners that are nearly invisible</li>
    <li>Removable for eating, brushing, and flossing</li>
    <li>No food restrictions</li>
    <li>Fewer dental visits than traditional braces</li>
    <li>Comfortable fit, no metal brackets or wires</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Our Invisalign Process</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Consultation</strong> – We’ll assess your smile and determine if Invisalign is right for you.</li>
    <li><strong>3D Digital Scanning</strong> – Using iTero® digital impressions, we’ll create a custom treatment plan.</li>
    <li><strong>Custom Aligner Creation</strong> – You'll receive your first set of aligners and instructions on how to wear them.</li>
    <li><strong>Progress Tracking</strong> – You’ll switch aligners every 1–2 weeks and visit us periodically to monitor results.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Trusted Invisalign Provider in North Potomac</h2>
  <p>As a <strong>Top 1% Diamond Invisalign Provider in North America</strong>, Dr. Richard Cantwell and the team at Potomac Crown Dentistry have helped hundreds of patients transform their smiles. We combine cutting-edge dental technology with years of Invisalign experience to ensure efficient, stunning results.</p>

  <h2>💬 Invisalign FAQs</h2>
  <p><strong>How long does Invisalign take?</strong><br />
  Treatment time depends on your case, but most patients see results in 6–18 months.</p>

  <p><strong>Is Invisalign painful?</strong><br />
  You may feel mild pressure for a day or two with each new set, but it’s generally more comfortable than braces.</p>

  <p><strong>Can I remove Invisalign anytime?</strong><br />
  Yes, but you should wear them 20–22 hours a day for best results.</p>

  <p><strong>Is Invisalign good for teens?</strong><br />
  Absolutely. We offer Invisalign Teen, which includes features like eruption tabs and compliance indicators.</p>

